1 A BILL for an Act to provide for a legislative management study relating to tribal land taxation.
2 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
3 SECTION 1. LEGISLATIVE MANAGEMENT STUDY - TRIBAL LAND TAXATION. During
4 the 2025-26 interim, the legislative management shall consider studying tribal land taxation
5 issues related to taxation of land owned by enrolled tribal members who reside within the
6 boundaries of any tribal reservation in this state. The study may include analysis of federal law,
7 judicial decisions concerning tribal taxation authority, state property tax exemptions related to
8 property of Native Americans, and the interaction between tribal sovereignty and state law. The
9 legislative management shall report its findings and recommendations, together with any
10 legislation required to implement the recommendations, to the seventieth legislative assembly.
